{
  "answer": "**The work is the *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, Chapter 3 (\"Chapter 3\" or *prāyaścitta-adhyāya*, \"On Expiation\").**[^1]\n\nThis chapter provides the precise anatomical inventory matching the query, including a man's body having **three hundred and sixty bones** (verse 84), **sixty-four teeth** (with sockets, verse 85), **twenty nails** (verse 85), **seventy-two ribs** (with sockets and nodules, verse 89), **forty-five bones** in the back (verse 88), **fifteen** in the neck (verse 88), and **seventeen** in the chest (verse 90); the body containing **seven hundred veins**, **nine hundred sinews**, **two hundred arteries**, and **five hundred muscles** (verse 100); **one hundred and seven vital spots** and **two hundred joints** (verse 102); and body hairs with sweat ducts numbering **fifty crores and four crores… and sixty-seven and a half lakhs** (verse 103).[^2]\n\nThe requested verses are:\n\n> His bodies are sixfold, and six skins support them;  \n> there are six limbs, and **three hundred and sixty bones**. // Yj_3.84 //[^3]\n\n> **Seven hundred veins, nine hundred sinews**,  \n> **two hundred arteries, and five hundred muscles**. // Yj_3.100 //[^4]\n\n[^1]: *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, Chapter 3, [translation](https://falsafa-corpus.vercel.app/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/03/translation/).\n\n[^2]: *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, Chapter 3, verses 84–90, 100, 102–103, [paragraphs](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/03/translation/#p-ac1be2).\n\n[^3]: *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, Chapter 3, [paragraph](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/03/translation/#p-ac1be2).\n\n[^4]: *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, Chapter 3, [paragraph](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/03/translation/#p-e42749).",
